<h2 id="2026-trends">📈 2026 Trends Shaping Ecommerce Tech</h2>

Several shifts are influencing stack decisions this year:

**AI that actually works.** After years of hype, AI-powered tools for customer service, inventory forecasting, and content generation have reached genuine utility. Gorgias, Kustomer, and dedicated AI tools now handle 30-50% of support tickets without human intervention.

**Consolidated commerce.** The line between retail, ecommerce, and marketplace sales continues to blur. Winning stacks treat all channels as unified operations rather than siloed businesses.

**Profitability focus.** The growth-at-all-costs era is definitively over. Tools that optimize for profit (Lifetimely, Segments, etc.) are replacing vanity metric dashboards.

**Privacy-first analytics.** Server-side tracking, first-party data, and probabilistic attribution have become table stakes